  "texts": [
    "Examples include major social media networks, video/image sharing platforms, collaborative economy platforms with public-facing profiles, app stores with browseable interfaces, and online marketplaces.",
    "In addition to hosting service obligations, online platforms must put in place complaint and redress mechanisms under Articles 17 and 18 as well as publish transparency reports under Article 13.",
    "Certain online platforms may also undergo risk assessments under Article 26 and have additional opt-in transparency duties regarding recommender systems under Article 29.",
    "• Very large online platforms or search engines (VLOPs or VLOSEs): Online platforms or search engines reaching an EU-wide threshold of over 10% of the EU population -set at around 45 million active monthly users.",
    "Ps such as Meta, YouTube, X, and TikTok qualify under Article 25 [51, 52]."
  ],
